snippet.textDisplay:
I'm not usually one to say things like this, but something tells me Ryan Newman's job on this Earth is not complete.
To survive an impact over the driver's compartment roof, to slide on the now completely exposed and unprotected driver's window at those speeds for that length.
I'm not a big God or church guy, but I believe we all witnessed some things that just may not ever be explained logically.
God bless this man and his family over the next few days, I hope he makes a full recovery.
